Introduction¶

Dataset Description¶

This data set contains information about 10,000 movies collected from The Movie Database (TMDb), The Movie Database (TMDb) is a community built movie and TV database, We love how they support their community and the passion with which they have built

Columns of tmdb_movies dataset:¶

  • id:a unique identifier for each movie.
  • imdb_id: a unique identifier for IMDB of movie
  • popularity: A numeric quantity specifying the movie popularity.
  • budget: The budget in which the movie was made.
  • revenue: The worldwide revenue generated by the movie.
  • original_title: The title of the movie before adaptation.
  • cast: The name of lead and supporting actors.
  • homepage: A link to the homepage of the movie.
  • director: the director of the movie
  • tagline: Movie's tagline.
  • keywords: The keywords or tags related to the movie.
  • overview: A brief description of the movie.
  • runtime: The running time of the movie.
  • genres: The genre of the movie, Action, Comedy ,Thriller etc.
  • production_companies: The production house of the movie.
  • release_date: The date on which it was released.
  • vote_count: count ratings te movie recieved
  • vote_average: average ratings the movie recieved.
  • release_year: the year which the movie released in
  • budget_adj: shows the budget associated movie
  • revenue_adj: shows the revenue associated movie

Question(s) for Analysis¶

  • what is the highest rated movie over all years?
  • what is the top eight popular movies?
  • which director have produced the best movies in 2010?
  • what is the average vote_count for movies?
  • which movie have the highest runtime?
  • what is the relationship between revenue and popularity
  • what is the relationship between revenue and budget
  • what is the relationship between budget and popularity
  • Which Movie Has The Highest profit?
  • Movies with most and least earned revenue

Research Question 10 : Movies with most and least earned revenue¶

In [71]:
import pprint
#defining the function
def calculate(column): 
    top= data[column].idxmax()
    top_info=pd.DataFrame(data.loc[top])
    
    low= data[column].idxmin()
    low_info=pd.DataFrame(data.loc[low])
    
    #collectin data in one place
    collect=pd.concat([top_info, low_info], axis=1)
    
    return collect

defining the function, for highest earned revenue, lowest earned revenue and collect data in one place

Conclusions¶

This was a very interesting data analysis. We came out with some very interesting facts about movies. After this analysis we can conclude following:

  • the highest rated movie over all years is The Story of Film: An Odyssey

  • the top eight popular movies are Jurassic World, Mad Max: Fury Road, Interstellar, Guardians of the Galaxy ,Insurgent ,Captain America: The Winter Soldier, Star Wars and John Wick

  • the directors which produced best movies in 2010 are Derek Frankowski, Sam Dunn|Scot McFadyen, Dean Wellins ,Richard Press , Asif Kapadia and Christopher Nolan

  • the average vote count for movies is 218.60074074074075

  • the movies which have highest runtime are The Story of Film: An Odyssey, Band of Brothers, Shoah, Planet Earth and The Pacific

  • there is positive relationship between revenue and popularity

  • there is positive relationship between revenue and budget

  • there is positive relationship between budget and popularity

  • movie which has the highest profit is avatar

  • we noticed that the story of film: an odyssey is the highest rated movie and highest runtime movie

  • star wars: the force awakens has the highest revenue which is 2068178225

  • avatar has the lowest revenue which is -2147483648

Limitations¶

  • id, imdb_id columns are similar column so we can get rid of one of them. I dropped imdb_id column which is not given any useful information for this analysis. also it's a string

  • i dropped budget_adj,revenue_adj columns as i will use budget and revenue columns instead

  • we replaced zero values with mean instead of dropping them because they are too many

  • data type of budget, revenue and runtime changed from int to float when replacing 0 to NaN in these columns
